# Hybrid Test Automation Framework

## Project Overview

This project is a Hybrid Test Automation Framework where Selenium, Pytest, Requests, Jenkins, Docker and Selenium Grid are used.

The framework automates:

- UI Testing
- API Testing
- End-to-End Validation
- Performance Checks
- Parallel Execution
- CI/CD Integration

The Notes Application: is the application that will be tested.
https://practice.expandtesting.com/notes/app

---

# Features Implemented

## UI Automation
- Login functionality validation
- Create note functionality
- Negative UI scenarios
The first one is a failure dialog box when capturing.Firstly, there is a capture failure dialog box.

## API Automation
- Login API
- Get Notes API
- Create Note API
- Delete Note API
- Negative API scenarios

## Hybrid Testing
This includes UI/ API End-to-End validation.This comprises End-to-End validation of UI + API.

## Reporting
- HTML Reports
- Allure Reports

## Parallel Execution
- Implemented using pytest-xdist

## CI/CD
- Jenkins Pipeline Integration
- GitHub Integration

## Docker & Selenium Grid
- Selenium Hub setup
- Chrome Node execution
- Firefox Node execution
- Remote browser execution

## Agentic Automation
- Intelligent waiting system
- Auto-retry mechanism

## MCP Implementation Layer
AI algorithms are used to simulate the test data.Test data is generated with the use of AI algorithms.
- Failure analysis support
- Locator suggestion mechanism

## Performance Engineering
Time the API response when calling the API.- Call the API and measure the API response time.
The duration that the user takes to load an UI page.
- Basic performance logging

