# Setup Instructions

## Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/adhithigoud21-hue/Testing_Notes_Application.git
```

---

# Create Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

Activate virtual environment:

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

---

# Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

# Running Tests

To run the entire test suite!To run any/all tests in the Test Suite!

```bash
pytest -v
```

---

## Run Parallel Tests

```bash
pytest -n 2
```

---

This is for the user to provide a test file to be run.Runs a user supplied test file.

```bash
pytest tests/test_login.py -v
```

---

# HTML Report Generation

```bash
pytest --html=reports/final_report.html --self-contained-html
```

Open report:

```text
reports/final_report.html
```

---

# Allure Report Generation

Generate results:

```bash
pytest --alluredir=allure-results
```

Open Allure report:

```bash
allure serve allure-results
```

---

# Selenium Grid Setup

## Start Docker Containers

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

---

## Verify Selenium Grid

Open:

```text
http://localhost:4444
```

---

# Jenkins Pipeline

Pipeline stages implemented:

- Checkout Code
- Install Dependencies
- Execute Tests
- Generate Reports
- Archive Artifacts

---

# Agentic Automation Features

If you are using Waits with intelligence, then you can use the WebDriverWait to create the Waits.Waits using WebDriverWait.
Support for flaky actions to be retried.

